node.title: Wanted man who fled from police in Northland found
node.description: A man with 12 outstanding warrants for his arrest in has now been found by police.
node.content:
["A man with 12 outstanding warrants for his arrest has now been found by police.", "", "
\nPhoto: RNZ / Richard Tindiller\n
", "Last week, police sought the 37-year-old after he failed to stop for them in the Whang\u0101rei suburb of Tikipunga, and fled the scene.", "Yesterday evening, police found him at an address on Auckland's North Shore and took him into custody.", "\"Our investigation remains ongoing into the incident last Thursday in Tikipunga, where a number of vehicles were damaged before the man fled.\"", "The 37-year-old was due to appear in Wait\u0101kere District Court today, facing 14 burglary charges and possession for supply of methamphetamine charge.", "Police said they could not rule out further charges being laid.", "They also found two modified firearms and a number of stolen property after recent search warrants.", "The recovered stolen items include a digger, worth about $50,000, that was allegedly stolen from Whang\u0101rei along with a trailer.", "Police thanked the public for their help and said they would work to return stolen items to their owners."]
